# React PDF Generation Best Practices (`@react-pdf/renderer`)

Use this rule whenever generating or modifying PDF templates, download flows, or PDF rendering logic.

## 1) Document and page structure rules

- Always keep `<Document />` as the root component.
- Only render `<Page />` as direct children of `<Document />`.
- Never nest `<Document />` inside any other react-pdf primitive.
- Use `<Page size="A4" orientation="portrait" wrap>` unless a specific requirement says otherwise.
- Keep sections composable: define small primitives like `HR`, `ChapterHeading`, `PageHeader`, `PageFooter`.
- Prefer semantic tree shape:
  - `Document` -> `Page` -> `View`/`Text`/`Image`/`Link`.

## 2) Metadata, security, and document-level options

Set document metadata when available:

- `title`, `author`, `subject`, `keywords`
- `creator`, `producer`, `language`
- `creationDate`, `modificationDate`
- `pdfVersion` (default `1.3`)
- `pageMode` (`useNone`, `useOutlines`, `useThumbs`, `fullScreen`, `useOC`, `useAttachments`)
- `pageLayout` (`singlePage`, `oneColumn`, `twoColumnLeft`, `twoColumnRight`, `twoPageLeft`, `twoPageRight`)

For protected files:

- Use `ownerPassword` before applying `permissions`.
- Optionally set `userPassword` for open protection.
- Restrict `permissions` explicitly (`printing`, `modifying`, `copying`, etc.) instead of relying on defaults.

## 3) Styling standards

- Prefer `StyleSheet.create` for shared, reusable styles.
- Use inline style objects only for tiny one-off dynamic overrides.
- Combine styles with arrays when needed: `style={[styles.base, dynamicStyle]}`.
- Use valid react-pdf units: `pt` (default), `in`, `mm`, `cm`, `%`, `vw`, `vh`.
- Use Flexbox/layout props supported by react-pdf (not web-only CSS assumptions).
- Keep typography readable in PDFs:
  - body text around `10-12`
  - line-height around `1.4-1.8`
  - strong contrast (`#333` on light background is safe)
- Use `debug` prop temporarily for layout troubleshooting; remove before merge.

## 4) Fonts and text rendering

- Register custom fonts before rendering with `Font.register`.
- Supported formats are only `TTF` and `WOFF`.
- Do not use variable OpenType fonts; register explicit sources per style/weight.
- If text uses italic/oblique/bold, ensure those variants are registered.
- Register all family variants together via `fonts: []` when possible.
- Use `Font.registerHyphenationCallback` when language or wrapping quality needs custom control.
- Disable hyphenation when required with:
  - `Font.registerHyphenationCallback(word => [word])`.

## 5) Layout, wrapping, and pagination

- Keep page wrapping enabled (`wrap={true}` default) for long documents.
- Understand wrapping behavior:
  - Breakable by default: `View`, `Text`, `Link`
  - Unbreakable by default: `Image`
- Use `wrap={false}` on blocks that must not split awkwardly.
- Use `break` on elements that must start on a new page (e.g., chapter starts).
- Use `fixed` for repeated headers, footers, and page numbers.
- Use `render={({ pageNumber, totalPages }) => ...}` for dynamic pagination text.
- Improve visual quality with widow/orphan controls:
  - `orphans`
  - `widows`
  - `minPresenceAhead` (useful to keep headings with following content).

## 6) Images, links, and navigation

Images:
- Prefer stable URLs or known local Node paths.
- `Image` supports JPG/PNG/base64/buffer/function sources.
- Keep `cache` enabled unless debugging fresh image fetch behavior.
- Use `srcSet`/`sizes` when resolution-sensitive assets are needed.

Navigation:
- Internal destinations: set `id` on target and link with `Link src="#id"`.
- Use `bookmark` to build table-of-contents style navigation.
- Assume some old viewers may ignore bookmarks/page mode/layout.

## 7) Web integrations and rendering flows

Use the right API by use case:

- `<PDFViewer />`: embedded preview iframe.
- `<PDFDownloadLink />`: simple user-triggered download.
- `<BlobProvider />`: access `blob`/`url` declaratively.
- `usePDF({ document })`: controlled rendering and explicit updates.
- `pdf(document).toBlob()`: imperative blob generation on web.
- Node/Express streaming: `renderToStream` and pipe response with `application/pdf`.

## 8) Performance and reliability

- Rendering is expensive; avoid unnecessary re-renders of large documents.
- Use `usePDF` update function for explicit regeneration boundaries.
- For browser documents with ~30+ pages, render inside a Web Worker to avoid blocking the UI thread.
- Keep document components pure and deterministic:
  - no random values during render
  - no mutable shared style objects
  - stable input data mapping.

## 9) Canvas and math usage

Canvas:
- Always define explicit `width` and `height` in style for `<Canvas />`.
- Keep `paint` deterministic and side-effect free.

Math:
- Use `@react-pdf/math` for LaTeX formulas.
- Use `inline` for in-text equations; default display mode for standalone equations.

## 10) Recommended template pattern

Follow this structure for report-like documents:

```tsx
import { Document, Page, View, Text, Image, StyleSheet, Font } from '@react-pdf/renderer';

Font.register({
  family: 'Oswald',
  src: 'https://fonts.gstatic.com/s/oswald/v13/Y_TKV6o8WovbUd3m_X9aAA.ttf',
});

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  body: { paddingTop: 50, paddingBottom: 65, paddingHorizontal: 65 },
  header: { fontSize: 8, textAlign: 'center', color: '#999', letterSpacing: 3, textTransform: 'uppercase' },
  text: { fontSize: 11, lineHeight: 1.7, textAlign: 'justify', color: '#333' },
  pageNumber: { position: 'absolute', bottom: 30, left: 0, right: 0, fontSize: 9, textAlign: 'center', color: '#999' },
});

const HR = () => <View style={{ borderBottomWidth: 1, borderBottomColor: '#8B4513', width: 60, marginVertical: 16 }} />;

const MyDoc = () => (
  <Document title="Report" author="Bhatti Agri-tech" pageMode="useOutlines" pageLayout="singlePage">
    <Page size="A4" style={styles.body} wrap>
      <Text style={styles.header} fixed>Report Header</Text>
      <HR />
      <Text style={styles.text}>Body content...</Text>
      <Text
        style={styles.pageNumber}
        render={({ pageNumber, totalPages }) => `${pageNumber} / ${totalPages}`}
        fixed
      />
    </Page>
  </Document>
);
```

## 11) Guardrails (do/don't)

Do:
- Keep PDF component code isolated in `pdf` modules.
- Keep style constants and helpers close to the template file.
- Validate long-text behavior with wrapping and page breaks.
- Test in at least two PDF viewers for navigation/metadata behavior.

Don't:
- Don't use unsupported CSS properties expecting browser behavior.
- Don't forget to register font variants you reference in styles.
- Don't render very large browser PDFs on the main thread.
- Don't assume all viewers honor `pageMode`, `pageLayout`, or bookmarks.
